<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="477" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,979,1330]" pageId="1" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1231,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="477">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vilela &amp; Farias &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2021" box="[435,533,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lencionii">
<emphasis box="[435,533,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="477">lencionii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(noun in genitive case) after Frederico Augusto de Atayde Lencioni (1970−), a notable Brazilian Odonatologist, whose friendship is priceless, for his 25+ years of odonatological work, his countless assistance in identification, loaning of specimens, and his advice through the years.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
